{
  "stem": "10588.3",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And what I couldn't understand, my mother [? breathed ?] literature, loved literature, poetry, she could say poems.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "In the bunker, she still [? started ?] to tell stories and to tell [? poetries ?] and tried to make it as normal as possible when we're there.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So when the Nazis invaded Poland, you know, they didn't start immediately.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "First start, [? this ?] [? year. ?] They invaded Poland.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "For us, the Holocaust started September 1, 1939.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And September 28, I believe, Warsaw was taken, the capital of Poland.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Till then, we were allowed to move from place to place.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In fact, people didn't know where to run.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Because, you see, you cannot always judge history by the past.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Because in the past, Russia had a far worst reputation for not being good to the Jews.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The [INAUDIBLE], you know, the [NON-ENGLISH] and others.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Excuse me.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 9 SECONDS] [DRINKS]",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So people didn't know.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Some people would run to Russia-- I mean, would run-- would run to Warsaw, because it's a bigger city.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "From Warsaw, people came.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "People were running back and forth.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They didn't know.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And this I remember distinctly.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My father was always very protective of his family, because my-- his two half-sisters, [INAUDIBLE] and [INAUDIBLE], they became orphans when they were very young.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they lived with my Aunt [?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Sula ?] and with my Uncle [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They were part of their household.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they treated them like their own children.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Because we were a very close family, always.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We took in my grandmother.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They took in their sisters.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So my father said he has to go to Pultusk, because of his sister.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we was going to run.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And my mother said something I never forget.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
